<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,694,1726]" box="[151,864,694,718]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ground color light brown with dark brown and black markings.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,694,1726]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Small, robust, brachypterous leafhoppers. Head medially longer than next to eyes, wider than pronotum; slightly produced medially, crown 2.5 times as wide as long; face slightly wider than long. Transclypeal sulcus interrupted in middle, antennal ledges oblique, clypellus widest in middle, lora elongate, ocelli on dorsal area slightly above imaginary line joining upper margin of eyes in facial view, closer to adjacent eye than to each other. Crown rounded to face. Face and crown granulate. Pronotum 1.4 times as long as head, 2.2 times as wide as median length, rather flat with one callus on either side of median line. Surface transversely rugose, anterior margin slightly rounded, posterior margin inwardly angulately curved. Scutellum flat, 0.75 times as long as pronotum, granulate. Forewings poorly developed, exposing four complete abdominal tergites in addition to genital capsule, caudally truncate with rounded lateral and mesal angles, venation obscure. Fore femora with intercalary row of setae well-developed; anteroventral seta AV 
<quantity box="[662,703,1054,1078]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
line with intercalary seta and AV 
<number box="[1099,1111,1054,1078]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
thickened (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1335,1054,1078]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1800,1823]" captionTargetBox="[178,1403,203,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[151,1436,193,1779]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 23. Skandagallia dietrichi gen. et sp. nov. A. Fore femur chaetotaxy; B. Male genital capsule, lateral view; C. Subgenital plates, ventral view; D. Aedeagus, dorsal view; E. Aedeagus apex; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Style &amp; connective, lateral view; H. Style, dorsal view; I. Connective, anterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215178/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[1305,1335,1054,1078]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
A). 
<collectingCountry box="[1380,1436,1054,1078]" name="India" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora with 
<number box="[301,317,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[334,344,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
macrosetae; hind tibiae PD 
<number box="[677,693,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="7.0">7</number>
± 
<number box="[712,723,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
, AD 
<number box="[789,805,1091,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="7.0">7</number>
, AV 
<number box="[868,882,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="5.0">5</number>
setae; metabasitarsus with 
<number box="[1202,1216,1090,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
platellae on apical transverse row of setae (
<figureCitation box="[423,506,1126,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[177,1422,231,1770]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[151,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 21. Leg chaetotaxy and anal segments of Agalliini. A, D. Purvigallia maculata gen. et sp. nov.; B, E. Sungallia truncata gen. et sp. nov.; C, F. Skandagallia dietrichi gen. et sp. nov. G – I. Sinoagallia serrata gen. et sp. nov. [A – C. Metabasitarsus, ventral view; D – F. Apex of hind tibiae, ventral view; G. Fore femur chaetotaxy; H. Anal tube, dorsal view; I. Anal tube, lateral view.]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215176/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
